{
  "texts": [
    "To every functor, 𝐹: Sp → Sp Goodwillie assigns a symmetric sequence 𝜕 * 𝐹 = {𝜕 𝑑 𝐹 } 𝑑∈N of spectra, in which we call the 𝑑-th term 𝜕 𝑑 𝐹, the 𝑑-th derivative of 𝐹.",
    "When the input functor is 𝑑-homogeneous, Goodwillie shows that it is completely determined by its 𝑑-th derivative.",
    "By [Goo03, Theorem 3.5 and §5], there is an equivalence Homog 𝑑 (Sp 𝜔, Sp) ≃ Sp 𝐵Σ 𝑑 between the ∞-category of 𝑑-homogeneous endofunctors of spectra and the ∞-category of spectra with an action of Σ 𝑑, the symmetric group on 𝑑 letters.",
    "Applying this classification of homogeneous functors to the splitting of Theorem 6.4 we obtain the following.Corollary 7.1.",
    "There is an equivalenceExc 𝑑 * (Sp 𝜔, Sp) Q ≃ 1≤𝑖≤𝑑 Sp 𝐵Σ 𝑖 Q of ∞-categories.Shipley's [Shi07] equivalence between 𝐻𝑅-module spectra and chain complexes of 𝑅-modules together with the identification of 𝐻 Q-module spectra with rational spectra induce the algebraic model of Theorem B upon the observation that there is an induced equivalenceSp 𝐵Σ 𝑖 Q = Fun(𝐵Σ 𝑖, Sp Q) ≃ Fun(𝐵Σ 𝑖, Ch Q) ≃ Ch(Q[Σ 𝑖])."
  ]
}